tachyon.client

Enum TachyonStorageType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TachyonStorageType>
      • tachyon.client.TachyonStorageType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<TachyonStorageType>

    public enum TachyonStorageType
extends Enum<TachyonStorageType>
    Specifies the type of data interaction with Tachyon. This option is for developers and advanced users. See WriteType and ReadType.
    • For a write operation, this determines whether the data will be written into Tachyon storage. Metadata will always be updated in Tachyon space.
    • For a read operation, this determines whether fully read blocks will be stored in Tachyon storage.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constant and Description
      NO_STORE

      PROMOTE

      STORE
